import sys

def main():
    n, m = map(int, sys.stdin.readline().split())
    t = list(map(int, sys.stdin.readline().split()))
    l = list(map(int, sys.stdin.readline().split()))

    t.sort()
    l.sort()

    i = 0
    j = 0
    count = 0
    while i < n and j < m:
        if t[i] <= l[j]:
            count += 1
            i += 1
        j += 1
    print(count)

if __name__ == '__main__':
    main()

def main():
    n, m = map(int, input().split())
    tasks = list(map(int, input().split()))
    intervals = list(map(int, input().split()))
    tasks.sort(reverse=True)
    intervals.sort(reverse=True)
    total = 0
    for i in range(n):
        if total >= m:
            break
        if tasks[i] <= intervals[total]:
            total += 1
    print(total)

main()

import sys

def main():
    n, m = map(int, sys.stdin.readline().split())
    tasks = sorted(map(int, sys.stdin.readline().split()))
    free_times = sorted(map(int, sys.stdin.readline().split()))

    task_index = 0
    free_time_index = 0
    completed = 0
    while task_index < n and free_time_index < m:
        if tasks[task_index] <= free_times[free_time_index]:
            task_index += 1
            free_time_index += 1
            completed += 1
        else:
            free_time_index += 1
    print(completed)

if __name__ == '__main__':
    main()

import sys

def main():
    n, m = map(int, input().split(' '))
    task_lens = list(map(int, input().split(' ')))
    quiet_lens = list(map(int, input().split(' ')))

    task_lens.sort()
    quiet_lens.sort()

    i = 0
    j = 0
    count = 0
    while i < len(task_lens) and j < len(quiet_lens):
        if task_lens[i] <= quiet_lens[j]:
            count += 1
            i += 1
        j += 1

    print(count)

if __name__ == '__main__':
    main()

def main():
    # Read in the input
    n, m = map(int, input().split(' '))
    tasks = list(map(int, input().split(' ')))
    quiet = list(map(int, input().split(' ')))

    # Sort the tasks and quiet intervals
    tasks.sort()
    quiet.sort()

    # Keep track of the number of tasks completed
    completed = 0

    # Keep track of the time of the last quiet interval
    lastQuiet = 0

    # Go through each task
    for task in tasks:
        # Go through each quiet interval
        for i in range(lastQuiet, m):
            # Check if the task can be completed in this quiet interval
            if task <= quiet[i]:
                # Increment the number of tasks completed
                completed += 1

                # Update the last quiet interval
                lastQuiet = i + 1

                # Move onto the next task
                break

    # Print out the number of tasks completed
    print(completed)

if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()
